ABOUT
=====

Here I create the scanned trialanine structures (from 0 to 330 every 30 deg)


HOW TO
======

To create the scanned structure:

```
cd input_scan/

~/sire.app/bin/python dihedral_scan.py ff99_trialanine/fit.prmtop ff99_trialanine/fit.rst7 dihedral.dat 30

```

the used prmtop does not matter at this stage

Then we retrieve the ff99SB energies and the mdcrd to use in Paramfit

```
cd  ../
cd energies
bash ff99SB_energies.sh

```
At the end we will have:

all_structures.mdcrd : all the valid structure ( whose energy < 25 kcal/mol) to use in Paramfit
energies_ff99SB.dat  : energies for each structure, to use for the fit

to visualize the f99 vs ff99SB energies use the ipython notebook script:
ff99vsff99SB.ipynb
